RECITALS WHEREAS, WindCo owns and operates a wind energy generation facility with a nameplate capacity of 30 MW (the WindCo Project ); WHEREAS, StorageCo (an affiliate of WindCo) owns and operates a battery energy storage facility with a nameplate capacity of 18 MW (the StorageCo Project , together with the WindCo Project, the Projects and each a Project ); WHEREAS, WindCo entered into a certain Interconnection Service Agreement by and among itself, PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ( PJM or Transmission Provider ) and Pennsylvania Electric Company ( PEC ), designated by PJM as Third Revised Service Agreement 937 and effective as of April 25, 2016 ( WindCo IA ) which provides for Interconnection Service (as defined in the WindCo IA) for the WindCo Project with an aggregate rated power output of up to 30 MWs; WHEREAS, StorageCo entered into a certain Interconnection Service Agreement by and among itself, PJM and PEC, designated by PJM as Original Service Agreement 4463 and effective as of April 25, 2016 ( StorageCo IA ), which provides for Interconnection Service (as defined in the Storage IA) for the Storage Project with an aggregate rated power output of up to 18 MWs (the Interconnection Service Agreement among WindCo, PJM and PEC, the WindCo IA and the Interconnection Service Agreement among StorageCo, PJM and PEC, the StorageCo IA , collectively, the IAs and each, an IA ); WHEREAS, StorageCo has a pending request for additional Capacity Interconnection Rights designated identified as queue position AE1-051; WHEREAS, StorageCo owns a separate step up transformer and revenue meter, and has its own unique asset identification number established with PJM; WHEREAS, the WindCo Project owns and intends to share with the StorageCo the use of certain premises (the Shared Premises ), on the terms and conditions set forth in this Agreement; and WHEREAS, WindCo owns certain personal property, fixtures, equipment and/or facilities used to interconnect the WindCo Project with the transmission system operated by PJM (as indicated in Schedule B to the WindCo IA) described in Exhibit A attached hereto that also are necessary to interconnect the StorageCo Project to the PEC transmission facilities operated by PJM at the Point of Interconnection as identified in Exhibit A (the Shared Facilities ); WHEREAS, the StorageCo Project will pay for, own, and construct certain electrical equipment upgrades to the interconnection facilities of the WindCo Project and the StorageCo Project at the Point of Interconnection identified in Exhibit A, and as may be needed; WHEREAS, the StorageCo Project and the WindCo Project agree that the WindCo shall be the Shared Facilities Manager to provide day-to-day, routine operation and maintenance services to StorageCo and WindCo for the Shared Premises and Shared Facilities, the expenses of which shall be covered by the WindCo, and the Shared Facilities Manager will provide such services for StorageCo and WindCo in accordance with the terms hereof; WHEREAS, the Parties shall receive any jurisdictional transmission and interconnection services from the Transmission Owner and/or Transmission Provider through the Shared Facilities pursuant to the StorageCo IA or the WindCo IA, as appropriate; and AGREEMENT NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the foregoing and of the mutual covenants and agreements contained herein, and for other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of which is hereby acknowledged, each of the Parties hereby agrees as follows: ARTICLE I DEFINITIONS The following capitalized terms will have the respective meanings set forth below: Additional Network Upgrades means any network upgrades beyond the Network Upgrades that are, or will be, required under the StorageCo and WindCo IA that are specifically required in connection with the use of the Shared Facilities. Affiliate of a Person means a Person that directly or indirectly through one or more intermediaries, controls, or is controlled by, or is under common control with, such Person. As used in this definition, control (including, with its correlative meanings, controlled by and under common control with ) shall mean possession, directly or indirectly, of power to direct or cause the direction of management or policies (whether through ownership of securities or partnership or other ownership interests, by contract or otherwise). Agreement means this Shared Facilities Agreement, as amended from time to time. Approved Credit Support means credit support acceptable to the Shared Facilities Manager for the ongoing payment obligations under this Agreement, the StorageCo IA, and the WindCo IA. Approved Shared Facilities O&M Budget has the meaning set forth in Section 6.9(a). Bankruptcy Event means, with respect to any Party, such Party: (a) voluntarily files a petition or otherwise commences, authorizes or acquiesces in the commencement of a proceeding or cause of action under any bankruptcy, insolvency, reorganization or similar law, or has any such petition filed or commenced against it by its creditors and such petition is not dismissed within sixty (60) days of the filing or commencement or an order for relief is entered; (b) makes an assignment or any general arrangement for the benefit of creditors; (c) otherwise becomes insolvent, however evidenced; (d) has a liquidator, administrator, receiver, trustee, conservator or similar official appointed with respect to it or any substantial portion of its property or assets; or (e) is generally unable to pay its debts as they fall due. Confidential Information has the meaning set forth in Section 11.4. Construction Start Date means, for any Project, the date on which commencement of on-site construction of (a) roads and (b) the initial wind turbine foundation for the Project have occurred. Default Rate shall mean the lesser of (i) the Prime Rate plus three percent (3%) per annum, or (ii) the maximum rate allowed by law. Demand has the meaning set forth in Section 7.4. Demanding Party has the meaning set forth in Section 7.4. Directly Assigned Expenses has the meaning set forth in Section 6.2. Disclosing Party has the meaning set forth in Section 11.4. Effective Date has the meaning set forth in the Preamble. Emergency shall mean any occurrence, in the reasonable judgment of a Party or the Shared Facilities Manager, that may arise that requires immediate action and (i) which constitutes a serious actual or potential hazard to the safety of persons or property, or (ii) may materially interfere with the safe, reliable, economical or environmentally sound operation of the Shared Premises and Shared Facilities. Event of Default has the meaning set forth in Section 9.1. FERC means the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission and any successor agency. GDPIPD shall mean the implicit price deflator for the gross domestic product as computed and published by the U.S. Department of Commerce. The figures to be used in this adjustment shall be those presented in the Gross Domestic Product: Third Quarter Final Press Release typically released in December of each calendar year by the United States Department of Commerce, Bureau of Economic Analysis. No subsequent revisions released by the United States Department of Commerce to those figures will be considered to affect or adjust the Inflation Adjustment Factor. Governmental Authority means any federal, state, local or other governmental, judicial, public or statutory instrumentality, tribunal, agency, authority, body or entity, or any political subdivision thereof or any regional transmission authority, having legal jurisdiction over the matter or person in question, and specifically includes the North American Electric Reliability Corporation (NERC) and regional electric reliability councils. IA or IAs has the meaning set forth in the Recitals. Indemnified Party has the meaning set forth in Section 4.1. Indemnifying Party has the meaning set forth in Section 4.1. Inflation Adjustment Factor shall mean a fraction, the numerator of which is the GDPIPD for the prior calendar year and the denominator of which is the GDPIPD for the next prior calendar year; provided that such fraction shall be converted to decimal format to be carried to five (5) decimal places. Laws means all applicable laws, statutes, ordinances, rules, regulations, decrees, policies, orders, permits, requirements, judgments, decisions, injunctions and findings of or issued by any Governmental Authority, including laws relating to health, safety and the environment. Losses has the meaning set forth in Section 4.1. Maximum Facility Output shall mean, for purposes of this agreement the maximum net electrical power output in megawatts specified by Transmission Provider at the Point of Interconnection. Non-Pledging Party has the meaning set forth in Section 8.3(iv). Party or Parties has the meaning set forth in the Preamble. Person means any individual, partnership, joint venture, company, corporation, limited liability company, limited duration company, limited life company, association, trust or other entity or organization, including a government or political subdivision or an agency or instrumentality thereof. Pledging Party has the meaning set forth in Section 8.3(iv). Point of Interconnection has the meaning set forth in the Recitals. Prime Rate means the rate of interest per annum publicly announced from time to time by JPMorgan Chase & Co. as its prime lending rate in effect at its principal office in New York City, provided, however, that if such prime lending rate is no longer publicly announced by JPMorgan Chase & Co., Prime Rate shall mean the rate of interest published from time to time in The Wall Street Journal or its successor publication as its prime lending rate in effect. Project means the electric generating and associated equipment and facilities of the StorageCo Project and/or the WindCo Project. Project Controlled Assets means, for each Project, the land and facilities that are part of the Project but are not Shared Premises or Shared Facilities. Pro Rata Share means, for each Party, the percentage interest of such Party in the Shared Expenses, calculated from time to time, equal to a whole number fraction, using a ratio equal to the nameplate capacity of the WindCo Project and StorageCo Project, respectively, divided by the combined nameplate capacity of the Projects, as such ratios may change from time to time to reflect current operating conditions of each Project; provided that the Pro Rata Shares for the WindCo Project and StorageCo Project will be 100% and 0%, respectively, until such time that StorageCo enters commercial operation. Prudent Industry Practices shall mean those practices, methods and acts that would be implemented and followed by a prudent operator of wind generating facilities similar to the Projects in the United States during the relevant time period, which practices, methods and acts, in the exercise of prudent and responsible professional judgment in the light of the facts known at the time the decision was made, could reasonably have been expected to accomplish the desired result consistent with good business practices, reliability and safety. In determining which practices, methods and acts constitute Prudent Industry Practices, due regard shall be given to, among other things, manufacturers warranties, contractual obligations, the requirements or guidance of Governmental Authorities and the Transmission Provider, applicable Laws, and the requirements of insurers, but in no event shall Prudent Industry Practices be interpreted to require any practice, method or act that violates applicable Laws. Recipient Party has the meaning set forth in Section 11.4. Related Parties shall mean, in the case of any Person, the partners, members, managers, officers, directors, employees, contractors, attorneys, financial advisors, agents and other advisors or representatives of such Person. Rules has the meaning set forth in Section 7.3. Secured Party shall mean, with respect to a Party, (i) the agent or lead bank or lending institution under a loan agreement with a Party or other entity secured by any of the Shared Facilities and Shared Premises, or all or a portion of a Party s interest in the Shared Facilities, (ii) the owner lessor or other entity acquiring a Project or undivided ownership interest therein pursuant to a lease financing, (iii) any other entity providing financing for a Project, including through tax equity financing, (iv) any other party acknowledged by such Party as a Secured Party in writing; provided, however, that no party shall be deemed a Secured Party entitled to the rights accruing to a Secured Party until such party gives written notice to each of the Parties along with an address for receipt of notices. Shared Expenses has the meaning set forth in Section 6.1. Shared Facilities has the meaning set forth in the Recitals. Shared Facilities Manager means the Person appointed manager of the Shared Facilities, which Person shall perform the obligations of Shared Facilities Manager as set forth in this Agreement and which Person shall be appointed, removed and replaced in accordance with Section 5.2 of this Agreement. The initial Shared Facilities Manager shall be WindCo. Shared Facilities Manager Fee has the meaning set forth in Section 6.1. Shared Facilities O&M Budget has the meaning set forth in Section 6.9(a). Shared Premises has the meaning set forth in the Recitals. StorageCo has the meaning set forth in the Preamble. StorageCo IA has the meaning set forth in the Recitals. StorageCo Project has the meaning set forth in the Recitals. Surrendering Party has the meaning set forth in Section 2.4. Term has the meaning set forth in ARTICLE III. Transfer means to sell, transfer, assign, set over, deliver, dispose of or otherwise demise an interest in tangible assets or intangible property, including this Agreement. Transmission Owner has the meaning set forth in the Recitals and any successor thereto. Transmission Provider has the meaning set forth in the Recitals and any successor thereto. WindCo has the meaning set forth in the Preamble. WindCo IA has the meaning set forth in the Recitals. WindCo Project has the meaning set forth in the Recitals. ARTICLE II GRANT OF SHARED FACILITIES AND PREMISES RIGHT 2.1 Grant. During the Term, WindCo hereby grants to StorageCo, on the terms and subject to the conditions hereof, the non-exclusive right to access and utilize the Shared Facilities and Shared Premises as may be reasonably necessary in connection with StorageCo s ownership, operation, and maintenance of the StorageCo Project. WindCo hereby acknowledges and agrees that StorageCo s right to access and utilize the Shared Facilities and Shared Premises is essential to the operations of the StorageCo Project. The right to access and utilize the Shared Facilities and Shared Premises granted to StorageCo hereunder shall vest in StorageCo as a contracting party hereunder without any transfer of title or leasehold interest in the Shared Facilities. In order to facilitate the shared use of the Shared Facilities and Shared Premises, the Parties agree that the installation, construction, testing, operation, inspection, maintenance, repair, alteration, relocation, removal, improvement or replacement of all or any portion of the Shared Facilities shall be done by or through WindCo as the Shared Facilities Manager. 2.2 Shared Premises. The Parties shall reasonably cooperate with each other in connection with their respective uses of the Shared Premises, and each Party shall use commercially reasonable efforts, consistent with Prudent Industry Practice, to limit any interference with the other Party s use and enjoyment of the Shared Premises. 2.3 Planned Outages. Each Party agrees that, (i) upon reasonable notice by the other Party, and (ii) subject to coordination with the Transmission Owner, it will, in conformity with the standards referred to herein, and without significant or unreasonable risk to the other Party, de-energize and isolate the Shared Facilities such that the Shared Facilities Manager can, in safety, make repairs or additions to the Shared Facilities as are necessary or desirable per the terms of this Agreement. Whenever possible, the Parties agree to coordinate their activities and make available all necessary personnel on a twenty-four (24) hour basis to de-energize and re-energize the Shared Facilities so as to reasonably minimize and avoid any disruption. The parties shall work with the Manager to coordinate and plan each planned outage at least 45 days in advance of such planned outage. ARTICLE III TERM The term of this Agreement (the Term ) will commence on the Effective Date, and shall continue in effect for the duration of the StorageCo IA and the WindCo IA. Notwithstanding the foregoing, the Agreement shall terminate, subject to obtaining any necessary prior FERC approvals for such termination, upon the first occurrence of one of the following: (i) a single Party becoming the owner of the entire ownership interest in all of the Shared Facilities and Shared Premises, or (ii) the mutual written agreement of all the Parties, with the consent of the then existing Secured Parties. ARTICLE IV INDEMNITY, USE AND COMPLIANCE 4.1 Cross Indemnity. (a) Each Party (an Indemnifying Party ) shall indemnify, defend and hold harmless the other Party and its respective Affiliates (excluding the relevant indemnitor, as applicable) and all of its respective officers, directors, employees, agents, partners, shareholders and representatives (an Indemnified Party ) from and against any and all losses, damages, liabilities, claims, judgments, liens, penalties, costs and expenses, including, without limitation, reasonable attorneys and consultants fees (collectively, Losses ), which may be imposed upon or incurred by such Indemnified Party or asserted against such Indemnified Party by any third person or entity (a) in connection with a breach of this Agreement, failure to comply in any material respect with applicable Law, or any grossly negligent or willful acts or omissions of or on behalf of the Indemnifying Party on or with respect to such Party s Project Controlled Assets at any time after the Effective Date, except to the extent caused by the Indemnified Party s gross negligence or willful misconduct, or (b) as a result of outages or curtailment of the Shared Facilities, other than in accordance with Section 5.5, proximately caused by the Indemnifying Party. (b) If for any reason whatsoever the Parties are or become jointly or jointly and severally liable to any third party for any obligation related to this Agreement and no Party is required to indemnify the other Parties under Section 4.1(a), the respective liability of each of the Parties, as among themselves, will be limited severally to their respective Pro Rata Shares. Without limiting the foregoing, the liability of each Party under this Section 4.1(b) will be in proportion to such Party's respective Pro Rata Shares, and to the extent any indemnification obligations of the Parties under this Article 4 relate to any Project Controlled Assets, any Party not owning any share of such Project Controlled Assets will not have any responsibility or liability for or with respect to any such indemnification obligations. Any Party that may incur joint or joint and several liability to a third party in excess of such Party's Pro Rata Share thereof as provided in this Section 4.1(b) shall be entitled to contribution and indemnity from the other Party on a proportionate basis. 4.2 Indemnification of Shared Facilities Manager. Each Party shall indemnify, defend, and hold harmless the Shared Facilities Manager and its Affiliates (excluding the relevant indemnitor, as applicable) and all of its respective officers, directors, employees, agents, partners, shareholders and representatives, from and against any and all Losses arising out of (i) the acts (or failures to act) of such Party or its officers, directors, employees, agents, members and representatives, hereunder or (ii) subject to Section 4.3, the acts of the Shared Facilities Manager pursuant to its authority under this Agreement, provided the liability of each Party under this subsection (ii) shall be in proportion to its Pro Rata Share of such liability; and the Shared Facilities Manager, its owners, officers, directors and employees shall not be liable to such Party or any third party for any obligation, liability, or commitment incurred by or on behalf of such Party in accordance with the provisions of this Agreement; provided, however, that the Shared Facilities Manager, its officers, directors and employees shall not be entitled to indemnification hereunder to the extent any action, claim, demand, cost or liability results from breach of this Agreement or from the Shared Facilities Manager s gross negligence or willful misconduct. 4.3 Indemnification by the Shared Facilities Manager. The Shared Facilities Manager shall indemnify, defend and hold harmless each Party and its Affiliates (excluding the relevant indemnitor, as applicable) and all of their respective officers, directors, employees, agents, partners, shareholders and representatives, from and against any and all Losses arising out of the Shared Facilities Manager s gross negligence or willful misconduct. 4.4 Lapse in the Availability and Operation of the Shared Facilities. The Parties acknowledge that in the event the Shared Facilities used to provide interconnection service become unavailable for any reason to carry energy produced by each Party across the Point of Interconnection, each Party s right to utilize the Transmission Provider s transmission system will be suspended for the duration of such unavailability. The Parties further acknowledge that in the event that any of the Parties ceases operations of the Shared Facilities, removes from service the Shared Facilities upon which each Party s interconnection service hereunder depends, or for any other reason the Shared Facilities become permanently unavailable to transmit energy produced by StorageCo s storage facility and/or WindCo s generating facilities, it shall be the Parties responsibility to acquire and install, or to obtain rights to utilize, other interconnection facilities necessary to enable the Parties to deliver energy produced by their generating facility to the Point of Interconnection. 4.5 Limitations on Liability; Waiver of Consequential Damages. The maximum aggregate liability of a Party for Losses under this Agreement shall not exceed an amount equal to $3,000,000. The maximum aggregate liability of the Shared Facilities Manager for Losses under this Agreement shall not exceed an amount equal to $180,000. In no event shall the liability of the Shared Facility Manager or a Party under this Agreement, as applicable, (other than liability arising out of acts or omissions constituting negligence, fraud, willful misconduct or breach of this Agreement by the Shared Facilities Manager or a Party) exceed, in any calendar year during the term hereof, the amount of actual insurance recoveries. Notwithstanding anything to the contrary in this Agreement, none of the Parties shall be entitled to, and each Party hereby waives any and all rights to recover consequential, incidental and punitive or exemplary damages, however arising, whether in contract, in tort or otherwise, under or with respect to any action taken in connection with this Agreement. 4.6 Environmental Compliance. Without limiting the scope of each Party s obligations under Section 4.1, each Party will, with respect to such Party s Project Controlled Assets, be responsible for all investigations, studies, clean up, corrective actions or responses or remedial actions required by any Governmental Authority now or hereafter authorized to regulate environmental or other matters or by any consent decree or court or administrative order now or hereafter applicable to such Party s use, operation or ownership of such Party s Project Controlled Assets. Each Party will have the right (but not the obligation, unless otherwise required above) to participate in the management and control of all investigations and any environmental clean-up, remediation or related activities relating to such Party s Project Controlled Assets. 4.7 No Waste or Nuisance; Maintenance; No Interference. No Party will use or permit the use of the Shared Facilities and Shared Premises in any manner that would create waste or nuisance that would have a materially adverse effect on any or all of the Shared Facilities and Shared Premises, or that would increase the rate or jeopardize the issuance or maintenance of any insurance policy relating to any or all of the Shared Facilities and Shared Premises. 4.8 Liens. Except as provided in Section 8.2, no Party will cause or permit any lien or encumbrance to be levied against or attached to the other Parties interests in the Shared Facilities and Shared Premises. 4.9 Project Controlled Assets Taxes. Each Party will pay all real and personal property taxes and assessments, general or special, levied against such Party s Project Controlled Assets. All such taxes and assessments will be paid before delinquency and before any fine, interest or penalty will become due or be imposed for their non-payment. 4.10 Insurance. Each Party shall, at its expense, maintain a commercial general liability insurance policy insuring it and the other Parties for bodily injury and property damage caused by such Party s use or operational management, as applicable, of the Shared Facilities and Shared Premises, with a limit not less than One Million Dollars ($1,000,000) per occurrence, accident or incident and an aggregate limit per policy term of not less than Two Million Dollars ($2,000,000). The Shared Facilities Manager shall maintain an all-risks property insurance policy covering the Shared Facilities and Shared Premises in an amount equal to the full replacement cost thereof with the cost of such policy allocated between the Parties in accordance with each Party s Pro Rata Share. Such policy shall name each Party as a loss payee as their interests may appear. Certificates of such insurance evidencing the coverages required by this Agreement shall be provided to the other Parties upon reasonable request. Each Party shall have the right to use a qualified program of self-insurance to meet the insurance requirements, and may also provide any such insurance pursuant to one or more blanket insurance policies maintained by such Party or its Affiliates. Notwithstanding the requirements above, the Parties may agree in writing to maintain jointly a general liability insurance policy and/or policy of casualty insurance covering the Shared Facilities and Shared Premises in the amounts specified above, with the costs of such jointly maintained policies allocated between the Parties in accordance with each Party s Pro Rata Share. 4.11 Reserved 4.12 Credit Support. Unless otherwise permitted by the Shared Facilities Manager, StorageCo and WindCo shall maintain Approved Creditworthiness or provide and maintain, at its expense, Approved Credit Support. ARTICLE V OPERATIONS AND MANAGEMENT 5.1 Interconnection Agreement Requirements. During the Term of this Agreement, the Shared Facilities Manager shall be the single point of contact with the Transmission Provider and the Transmission Owner as to all issues affecting both Projects or for issues specifying the need for a single point of contact under all applicable IAs. All disputes between the Parties to this Agreement shall be resolved between the Parties as set forth in Article 7. StorageCo and WindCo as Parties shall permit the Shared Facilities Manager an opportunity to review and comment on, and approve (as to the use of Shared Facilities and the role of the Shared Facilities Manager) any amendments to IAs prior to finalization thereof. 5.2 Appointment, Removal and Replacement of Shared Facilities Manager. WindCo is hereby appointed as the Shared Facilities Manager. (a) The Shared Facilities Manager shall hold such position until (i) it resigns for convenience and without any liability to the Parties upon at least ninety (90) days prior written notice to the Parties, (ii) it is removed for convenience upon at least ninety (90) days written notice to the Shared Facilities Manager by the Parties, (iii) it is removed for cause in the event of any bad faith, gross negligence, recklessness or willful misconduct in connection with performance of its duties hereunder upon notice from the Parties or (iv) StorageCo ceases operation or desires to assign or transfer its interconnection rights to another party. (b) If the Shared Facilities Manager is removed for any of the reasons set forth in Section 5.2(a), then StorageCo, will either serve as Shared Facilities Manager or select a replacement that is experienced and qualified to perform the duties of the Shared Facilities Manager for similar facilities, as set forth herein. StorageCo shall notify WindCo in writing within fifteen (15) days of receipt of the written notice set forth in Section 5.2(a) if it plans to serve as Shared Facilities Manager or select a replacement. (c) The Shared Facilities Manager shall, in good faith, continue to undertake its duties and obligations as the Shared Facilities Manager until such time as a successor Shared Facilities Manager is appointed hereunder and accedes to its responsibilities under this Agreement. 5.3 Maintenance of the Shared Facilities and Shared Premises. The Shared Facilities Manager agrees to perform and provide with respect to the Shared Facilities and Shared Premises professional, supervisory, managerial, administrative and operational responsibilities in accordance with the standards set forth in Section 5.4. 5.4 Performance Standard. Subject to the limitations or restrictions set forth in this Agreement, each Party shall perform its respective obligations (i) in accordance with this Agreement, (ii) in compliance with all Laws, (iii) in accordance with Prudent Industry Practices. Without limiting the foregoing, each Party shall operate and maintain its Project Controlled Assets acting as a prudent operator and manager and otherwise (i) in accordance with any applicable IA, the applicable power purchase agreement, any financing agreement or other material agreement relating to such Party s Project, and (ii) without causing a material adverse effect on the other Parties unless permitted under a build-out agreement between or among the Parties. Each Party shall, to the fullest extent commercially reasonable and subject to Prudent Industry Practices, (i) limit any interference with the use and enjoyment by the other Parties of its rights in and to the Shared Facilities and Shared Premises, and (ii) except in the event of an Emergency or as otherwise agreed between the Parties with respect to planned outages, (A) schedule during an off-peak and/or low wind period any required disconnection of the Shared Facilities or a Party s Project to conduct maintenance and repair activities in order to minimize the impact on the Projects of the other Parties, and (B) provide prior written notice to the other Parties of commencement of such maintenance and repair activities together with a reasonably detailed description thereof, including dates and times of such maintenance and repair activities, and any anticipated disconnection. The duties to be performed by the Shared Facilities Manager as set forth herein shall not constitute the Shared Facilities Manager as an architect, engineer, or construction contractor, nor impose upon the Shared Facilities Manager any obligation to assume, render to, or perform on behalf of StorageCo any responsibilities, duties, services, or activities assumed or rendered by any architect, engineer, or construction contractor employed on any project nor impose upon the party any liability with respect thereto. 5.5 Coordination (a) Curtailment. (i) Each Party shall comply with Section 5.9 with respect to Transmission Provider directives, including curtailment. (ii) The Parties shall interrupt or reduce deliveries of electrical power over the Shared Facilities if necessary to do so: (A) in order to maintain, repair, replace, remove, investigate, inspect or test any part of the Shared Facilities or Projects in accordance with the terms of this Agreement, after reasonable notice to and agreement by the Parties as to the timing and duration of the curtailment; (B) due to an Emergency; or (C) if the Shared Facilities Manager is ordered to do so by Transmission Provider other than through routine market dispatch signals, any Governmental Authority or regulatory authority with jurisdiction over the Projects or the Shared Facilities. Curtailment pursuant to Section 5.5(a)(ii)(C) shall be referred to herein as Directed Curtailment. (iii) The Parties shall limit the length of any interruption or curtailment pursuant to Section 5.5(a)(ii) to that time strictly necessary to correct the problem or comply with the applicable Interconnection Agreement. Any such interruption or curtailment shall be applied to each Project in accordance with the wind farm management system and software in place at the time. Any interruption or curtailment pursuant to Section 5.5(a)(ii)(A) shall be made to the extent commercially reasonable during periods that balance both low or no winds and low energy prices so as to minimize potential loss of revenue of the Parties(s) being curtailed. (iv) In the event of a Directed Curtailment, the Shared Facilities Manager shall determine and communicate to StorageCo or its respective agents the appropriate reduction for StorageCo, and StorageCo shall comply with such instructions. (v) The Shared Facilities Manager shall document the calculations relating to any curtailment described above and upon request from StorageCo, the Shared Facilities Manager shall provide it with documentation evidencing such calculations. (vi) To implement Directed Curtailments in the amounts determined pursuant to Section 5.5(a)(iv), the Shared Facilities Manager shall have the right and discretion to take the following actions: (A) call StorageCo s Market Participant and direct them to curtail the allocated amount of curtailment for that Project, or (B) override the maximum output signal being sent to StorageCo s Project with the calculated and allocated cap for that Project. If reduction in output as directed under either (A) or (B) above does not commence within five (5) minutes of the occurrence of (A) or (B), as applicable, or Emergency conditions otherwise require, the Shared Facilities Manager shall have the option to operate such Project s main circuit breaker to take such Project off-line. (vii) In the event that a Project s output exceeds either (A) applicable curtailment signals, or (B) the then maximum output consistent with dispatch requirements by more than 10 MWs in any rolling sequence of four (4) consecutive 5-minute dispatch intervals, then the Shared Facilities Manager shall have the authority to call the Party s Market Participant and direct them to reduce output to the appropriate maximum output. In the event such reduction in output does not commence within five (5) minutes following the Shared Facilities Manager s contact with the Party s Market Participant, the Shared Facilities Manager shall have the option to operate such Project s main circuit breaker to take such Project off-line. (viii) The Parties shall coordinate to design and install control system(s) consistent with Transmission Provider and Transmission Owner criteria to ensure that the total Maximum Facility Output at the Point of Interconnection is not exceeded. The incremental cost of the development and construction of such control system(s) shall be Directly Assigned Expenses allocated to StorageCo. If the combined output of the WindCo Project and StorageCo Project exceed the Maximum Facility Output at any given time, the WindCo Project shall take dispatch priority and may operate at its full output, and the StorageCo Project shall be curtailed for the duration of this condition as necessary so as not to exceed the aggregate Maximum Facility Output at the Point of Interconnection. After initial installation and commissioning, these control system(s) will be considered Shared Facilities and any operations and maintenance costs will be included by the Shared Facilities Manager as Shared Expenses in the Shared Facilities O&M Budget. (b) Data. The real time telemetry data that StorageCo and/or its Market Participant provides to the Shared Facility Manager may include, if requested by Shared Facilities Manager, information such as the Project s dispatch interval forecast of net output, dispatch signal, etc. WindCo shall, if requested by StorageCo, provide the Shared Facility Manager with the WindCo Project s interval forecast of net output consistent with forecasts submitted to the Transmission Provider. (c) Design Plans. Upon request, the Parties shall submit to the Shared Facilities Manager for prior approval, which approval shall not be unreasonably withheld, the design and construction plans for the substation and interconnection facilities, and the design, construction and operating plan and procedures relating to connection of the WindCo Project with the Shared Facilities and any related equipment and facilities of StorageCo. (d) Priority. WindCo hereby agrees that the operations of the StorageCo Project, including but not limited to receiving and charging electric energy from the grid and storing it for later injection to the grid, shall take precedence and will not be interfered by any later built electric storage facility owned and developed by WindCo, its affiliates, or other parties with permission from WindCo that take charging interconnection service through the same Point of Interconnection as the WindCo Project. (e) Additional Interconnection Service or Studies. The Parties agree that either Party may request additional interconnection service at the Point of Interconnection or other interconnection studies from the Transmission Provider for the benefit of their respective facilities, including, but not limited to, one or more of the following: increased Maximum Facility Output, increased Capacity Interconnection Rights (including those certain rights associated with StorageCo s queue position AE1-051), increased seasonal interconnection service of any time, addition or replacements of generating units, or modifications to the electrical characteristics of a facility. The non-requesting party shall cooperate using commercially reasonable efforts, to provide technical, operations, or other data as may be required for such a request or shall allow the requesting party to measure and collect any required data. The requesting party shall be solely responsible for and shall pay any costs associated with increasing interconnection service or requesting interconnection studies by the Transmission Provider, and for any Additional Network Upgrades identified as a result. 5.6 Disconnection from Shared Facilities. A Project shall be disconnected from the Shared Facilities if disconnection is necessary for safety in order to perform maintenance to any portion of the Shared Facilities or in the event of an Emergency. No Party shall be liable to any other Party for lost production or revenue that occurs as a result of any disconnection or outage of the Shared Facilities in accordance with this Section 5.6. 5.7 Specific Authority. Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, and subject to the limitations of authority of the Shared Facilities Manager in Section 5.8 below or otherwise set forth in this Agreement, in addition to the authority otherwise granted herein, the Shared Facilities Manager shall have the power, without further consent or approval of the other Party, to do any of the following: (a) to negotiate, enter into on behalf of the Parties, and administer agreements with third party contractors, or to employ persons, and to otherwise expend monies necessary for the management, operation, maintenance, and repair of the Shared Facilities and Shared Premises in accordance with this Agreement; provided, however, that (i) such engagement and any fees paid to such third party contractor thereunder shall be in accordance with the Approved Shared Facilities O&M Budget, (ii) with respect to any agreement with a third party contractor that is an Affiliate of the Shared Facilities Manager, the Shared Facilities Manager enters into such agreement on an arms-length basis and (other than with respect to agreements the aggregate value of which does not exceed $200,000 during the Term hereof) with the prior written consent of all Parties, (iii) no such third party contractor engagement shall relieve the Shared Facilities Manager of its rights or obligations set forth in this Agreement, and (iv) any such agreements or other actions shall comply with all applicable financing documents; (b) to pay and collect on behalf of the Parties amounts due in connection with the Shared Facilities and Shared Premises, but only in accordance with the Approved Shared Facilities O&M Budget; (c) to commit to the expenditure of or spend up to and including Six Hundred Thousand Dollars ($600,000) in the aggregate (including the costs of installation and expediting fees) for and on behalf of the Parties to repair the Shared Facilities and Shared Premises due to an Emergency; provided that the Shared Facilities Manager gives concurrent notice by facsimile and electronic mail to the Parties benefiting from such Shared Facilities and Shared Premises regarding the nature and amount of the expenditure as soon as reasonably practicable after the estimated amount of the expenditure is known by the Shared Facilities Manager, but in any event no later than the time the Shared Facilities Manager commits to the expenditure; (d) to negotiate with, and represent the Parties interests before, any Governmental Authority regarding property valuation and real property taxes (if any) related to Shared Facilities and Shared Premises; provided that any agreements or settlements with respect to the foregoing are approved by the Parties; and (e) to execute, acknowledge, and deliver any and all instruments and take such other steps as are reasonably necessary to effectuate the foregoing and as are consistent with the terms of this Agreement, including Section 5.8 and any other limitations set forth herein. 5.8 Limitation on Authority. The Shared Facilities Manager shall not take any of the following actions without the prior written approval of all Parties with a beneficial interest affected by the action: (a) create or cause to be created any lien on any of the Shared Facilities and Shared Premises; (b) amend or modify the terms of this Agreement, or any other agreement that affects any Party s rights hereunder to develop, own, and operate its Project; (c) sell, assign, mortgage, encumber, convey, or otherwise transfer all or any portion of a Party s interest in the Shared Facilities and Shared Premises, or any components of the Shared Facilities and Shared Premises; (d) borrow funds or otherwise incur indebtedness on behalf of a Party; (e) procure any insurance coverage that is less than the coverages required by this Agreement; (f) commit to expenditures in excess of Two Hundred Thousand Dollars ($200,000) per calendar year for each Party or Six Hundred Thousand Dollars ($600,000) per calendar year in the aggregate for and on behalf of the Parties except for repairs to the Shared Facilities and Shared Premises due to an Emergency; (g) incur an expense of more than One Hundred Fifty Thousand Dollars ($150,000) in any single instance or cumulative expenses of more than Two Hundred Fifty Thousand Dollars ($250,000) in the aggregate in any calendar year that is not included in the Approved Shared Facilities O&M Budget; (h) adopt or amend or modify the Approved Shared Facilities O&M Budget; (i) make any offer or enter into any contract, letter of intent or agreement with respect to the zoning classification or other zoning or land use restrictions on behalf of the Parties; or (j) do any act that is specified as being beyond the authority of a Party under this Agreement, or in contravention of, or that will otherwise cause a Party to be in default under this Agreement. All performance by the Shared Facilities Manager in relation to the Shared Facilities and Shared Premises will constitute the performance by the applicable Party of such Party s obligations under this Agreement relating thereto; provided, however, that upon the default by the Shared Facilities Manager of any such obligation, the applicable Party will remain obligated to perform such obligation. 5.9 Market Operations. (a) Each Party shall be required to appoint its own Market Participant, and that Market Participant shall be responsible for all schedule coordination and communication telemetry with the Transmission Owner and the Transmission Provider related to scheduling, provided that the Parties agree to follow all Directed Curtailment instructions. (b) Separate Commercial Pricing Nodes in the Transmission Provider's market model shall be established for each of the Projects and each Project will be responsible for offering its Project into the market, for settlement of cleared energy sales, and for responding separately to the Transmission Provider's dispatch instructions. 5.10 No Jurisdictional Service. The Parties acknowledge that none of the Parties is providing interconnection or transmission service, and rather that the Parties are, or will be receiving interconnection service under the StorageCo IA and the WindCo IA, and that the Parties can obtain transmission service, if desired, from the Transmission Owner and the Transmission Provider. ARTICLE VI SHARED EXPENSES; PAYMENTS; O&M BUDGET 6.1 Shared Expenses. Each Party shall be responsible for and shall pay its Pro Rata Share in rents and other payments due to landowners or otherwise accruing under leases for the Shared Premises resulting from or attributable to the installation, operation or placement of the Shared Facilities on the Shared Premises (the Shared Expenses ). Shared Expenses do not include Directly Assigned Expenses. Upon becoming a Party and until such Party ceases to be a Party hereunder, the Parties shall reimburse the Shared Facilities Manager for all reasonable direct and indirect labor and out-of-pocket expenses including, but not limited to, travel, telephone, facsimile, and postage of the Shared Facilities Manager, payable monthly in arrears, including overhead expenses. Each Party shall be liable for its Pro Rata Share of any fees due to landowners relating to the Shared Facilities. Unless as otherwise noted in this Agreement, each Party shall be solely responsible for any costs incurred under such Party s IA, and such costs shall not be included in Shared Expenses. 6.2 Directly Assigned Expenses. WindCo shall be solely responsible for and shall pay the expenses relating to the use, maintenance, repair, and inspection of the Shared Facilities and Shared Premises. StorageCo shall be solely responsible for and shall pay any incremental costs including but not limited to the control system(s) discussed in section 5.5(a)(viii) and the cost of Additional Network Upgrades, as may be required, relating to the interconnection of the Shared Facilities to the Transmission Owner s transmission system. Notwithstanding the provisions of this Article 6, any costs, claims, losses or other liabilities attributable to a particular Party may be directly assigned for one hundred percent (100%) cost responsibility of that Party ( Directly Assigned Expenses ). 6.3 Expenses Beyond the Scope of this Agreement. The Parties acknowledge and agree that the costs and expenses that may arise with respect to construction and operation or required amendments to this Agreement caused by a non-Party seeking use of any of the Shared Facilities or Shared Premises shall be borne by and be the sole responsibility of such non-Party. 6.4 Invoicing, Late Payments. The Shared Facilities Manager shall deliver a detailed invoice to the Party for their respective Pro Rata Share of the applicable Shared Expenses and any Directly Assigned Expenses on a monthly basis, on or before the tenth (10th) day of each month, for the actual amount incurred for all Shared Expenses under Section 6.1 for the immediately preceding month. The Parties shall pay to the Shared Facilities Manager the amount of each invoice within thirty (30) days after the date of the Shared Facilities Manager s issuance of each such invoice. If a Party fails to pay all or any portion of any amount owed to the Shared Facilities Manager under this Agreement by its due date for any reason whatsoever, then such Party shall, in addition to such unpaid amount, pay interest on the unpaid amount which shall accrue at a rate equal to the Default Rate from the due date therefor until such amount has been paid in full. 6.5 Reserved 6.6 Maintenance or Records. The Shared Facilities Manager shall maintain books and records in sufficient detail to verify amounts due and payable hereunder for a period of not less than three (3) years after the end of the calendar month to which they relate, and all such books and records shall be available for inspection and/or copying by the Parties and its Secured Parties or its authorized representative at the cost and expense of such party and at reasonable times during regular business hours, upon reasonable notice to the Shared Facilities Manager. 6.7 Provision of Records. The Shared Facilities Manager shall, from time to time, provide reports to the Parties sufficient to keep the Parties reasonably apprised as to significant matters concerning the maintenance and repair of the Shared Facilities and Shared Premises, including such matters related thereto which may have a material impact on the operation, maintenance or repair of each Party s Project. 6.8 Quarterly Reports. With respect to each Party, following the Construction Start Date of such Party s Project, the Shared Facilities Manager shall provide, upon request and no more frequently than quarterly, to each Party a report on or before the fifteenth (15th) day of the following quarter which shall provide each Party with such information necessary to keep the Parties reasonably apprised of the maintenance and repair of the Shared Facilities, including such matters related thereto which may have a material impact on the operation, maintenance or repair of each Party s Project. 6.9 Shared Facilities O&M Budget (a) On or prior to ninety (90) days prior to the beginning of each calendar year during the term hereof, the Shared Facilities Manager shall prepare and submit to the Parties a proposed budget for the following calendar year for operation, maintenance, and repair of the Shared Facilities and Shared Premises in accordance with this Agreement (each, a Shared Facilities O&M Budget ), which shall include, at a minimum, the Shared Facilities Manager Fee, billing rates, estimated cost, based on time and materials and all fees and reimbursable costs contemplated in this Agreement for anticipated operation and maintenance services and repairs to be provided by the Shared Facilities Manager during each month of the following year, including any known Shared Expenses and known Directly Assigned Expenses and any costs and expenses incurred relating to credit support required in connection with any Shared Facilities. The Shared Facilities O&M Budget shall set forth the respective amounts allocated to the Parties in accordance with Sections 6.1 and 6.2. When approved pursuant to subparagraph (b) below, the Shared Facilities O&M Budget shall be the Approved Shared Facilities O&M Budget for such year. The first Shared Facilities O&M Budget shall be delivered to the Parties on or before the date that is forty-five (45) days following the Effective Date, unless otherwise agreed by the Parties. (b) The Parties shall give their approval or disapproval of the Shared Facilities O&M Budget no later than thirty (30) days after receipt thereof from the Shared Facilities Manager. If the Parties object to all or any portion of the proposed Shared Facilities O&M Budget, the Parties shall furnish the Shared Facilities Manager in writing, the reasons for such objections and shall immediately commence discussions with the Shared Facilities Manager in an effort to reach an Approved Shared Facilities O&M Budget. Upon such agreement, the Shared Facilities Manager shall revise the Shared Facilities O&M Budget with respect thereto. If the Parties approve the Shared Facilities O&M Budget, the Shared Facilities O&M Budget will be the Approved Shared Facilities O&M Budget for the following year. If the Parties are unable to reach an agreement with respect to the Shared Facilities O&M Budget prior to the beginning of the calendar year, the Approved Shared Facilities O&M Budget for the previous calendar year (or the last Approved Shared Facilities O&M Budget if the Shared Facilities O&M Budget for the prior year was not approved), increased per year by the Inflation Adjustment Factor, shall apply; provided, however, that any single extraordinary expense in excess of Forty Five Thousand Dollars ($45,000) contained in such budget shall not be incurred without the prior approval of the Party. 6.10 Shared Facilities Manager Expenses. The Shared Facilities Manager shall be paid or reimbursed, to the extent inconsistent with the Approved Shared Facilities O&M Budget or when such costs exceed the threshold set forth in Section 6.9, as approved in advance by the Parties, for any unscheduled maintenance and repairs to and replacements of the Shared Facilities performed by the Shared Facilities Manager on behalf of the Parties at the Shared Facilities Manager s cost, including overhead expenses. Except in the event of an Emergency, the Shared Facilities Manager shall have the right to pre-invoice the Parties for any materials and components required to be provided hereunder, and not to proceed with the acquisition of such materials and components unless payment has been received by the Shared Facilities Manager for such materials and components. In the event the Shared Facilities Manager does not receive payment for any such pre-invoices, the Shared Facilities Manager may advance its own funds for the purchase of any such materials and components if the Shared Facilities Manager determines it is prudent to do so, and in such event, the Parties shall promptly, upon receipt of the applicable one or more invoices, deliver to the Shared Facilities Manager an amount equal to its Pro Rata Share of the invoiced amount, plus interest at the Default Rate. 6.11 Other Expenses Caused By Parties. Notwithstanding the provisions of this Article 6, any costs, claims, losses or other liabilities arising from the actions or inactions of a Party in violation or breach of the covenants herein shall be the responsibility of such Party. ARTICLE VII DISPUTE RESOLUTION 7.1 Dispute Resolution and Procedures. All disputes between or among any of the Parties shall be resolved in accordance with the dispute resolution procedures set forth in this Article 7. Notwithstanding the foregoing, (a) any of the Parties may at any time seek injunctive relief from a court of competent jurisdiction in accordance with Section 9.2(b) of this Agreement, and (b) nothing herein shall prevent any Party from defending or pursuing any claim in a court or other proceeding against a third party. 7.2 Notice; Meeting and Confer. In the event a dispute arises regarding the application or interpretation of any provision of this Agreement, the Party alleging the dispute shall promptly notify the other Parties of the dispute in writing. If the Parties shall have failed to resolve the dispute within ten (10) days after delivery of such written notice, each Party shall, within five (5) days of receipt of a written demand from the other Party to do so, direct a member of its senior management to confer in good faith within five (5) days with a member of senior management of the other Parties to resolve the dispute. Should the Parties be unable to resolve the dispute to their mutual satisfaction within fifteen (15) days, each Party shall have the right to pursue the resolution of such dispute in accordance with the provisions of Section 7.3. In no event shall the Transmission Owner or Transmission Provider be asked to resolve a dispute between or among the Parties. 7.3 Agreement to Mediate Disputes. The Parties shall engage in good-faith mediation to resolve disputes as to any controversy, claim, or dispute between the Parties arising out of or related to this Agreement or the breach thereof that cannot be settled pursuant to Section 7.1(a) within 30 days before resorting to litigation or some other dispute resolution procedure. The mediator will be selected based on the mutual agreement of the Parties. The mediation process shall be confidential based on terms acceptable to the mediator and the Parties. 7.4 Commencement of Proceedings. Any Party desiring arbitration (the Demanding Party ), rather than mediation pursuant to Section 7.3, shall serve on the other Party and its Secured Parties, and the American Arbitration Association in accordance with the Rules, its demand for arbitration (the Demand ), accompanied by the name of the person chosen by the Demanding Party to select an arbitrator. The other Party shall choose a person to select an arbitrator, and the persons so chosen shall select the arbitrator. If the Party upon whom the Demand is served fails to choose a person to select an arbitrator and advise the Demanding Party of its selection within fifteen (15) days after receipt of the Demand, the person chosen by the Demanding Party shall select the arbitrator. If the persons chosen by the Parties to select the arbitrator cannot agree upon an arbitrator within ten (10) days after the designation of the second person, the arbitrator shall be selected in accordance with the Rules. The arbitration proceedings provided hereunder are hereby declared to be self-executing, and it shall not be necessary to petition a court to compel arbitration. 7.5 Location. All arbitration proceedings shall be held in Chicago, Illinois. 7.6 Filing Deadlines. Notice of the Demand shall be filed in writing with the other Party and with the American Arbitration Association. The Demand shall be made within a reasonable time after the claim, dispute or other matter in question has arisen, and in no event shall it be made after the date when institution of legal or equitable proceedings based on such claim, dispute or other matter in question would be barred by the applicable statutes of limitations. 7.7 Consent to Jurisdiction; Waiver of Jury Trial. Each Party irrevocably and unconditionally (a) agrees that any suit, action or other legal proceeding based upon, arising out of or in connection with this Agreement shall be brought in the state or federal courts located in Chicago, Illinois (or, only if the state or federal courts located in Chicago, Illinois decline to accept jurisdiction over a particular matter, any state or federal court within the State of Illinois), (b) consents to the jurisdiction of any such court in any such suit, action or proceeding, and (c) waives any objection that such Party may have to the laying of venue of any such suit, action or proceeding in any such court. Each Party knowingly, voluntarily, and irrevocably waives any right that such Party may have to a trial by jury in respect of any claim based upon, arising out of or in connection with this Agreement. ARTICLE VIII TRANSFER OR ASSIGNMENT OF INTERESTS 8.1 Transfer. No Party to this Agreement may Transfer such Party s interest in this Agreement without the consent of the other Party to this Agreement; provided, however, consent from the other Party to this Agreement shall not be required in the event of a Transfer by a Party of all or part of any Project Controlled Asset if, as conditions to the Transfer, (i) the new owner will be assigned and will assume the Transferring Party s interest in this Agreement, in whole or in part according to whether the Transfer was total or partial, (ii) the new owner will become a Party to this Agreement and will assume in writing for the benefit of all other Parties (including the Shared Facilities Manager) all future rights, liabilities and obligations of the Transferring Party, (iii) the new owner will, immediately following such Transfer, have creditworthiness that is equal to or greater than the Approved Creditworthiness or have provided Approved Credit Support, and provided, further, however, any such Transfer shall be subject to receipt of any required regulatory approvals. Following any permitted Transfer under this Article 8, the Transferring Party shall be released from all subsequent liabilities and obligations under this Agreement arising from and after such Transfer (but not from any liabilities or obligations that arose prior to such Transfer). Each Party may collaterally assign such Party s interest in this Agreement and Facilities to lenders as it sees fit, provided the Project Controlled Asset is collaterally assigned concurrently therewith, but no such assignment will subordinate or otherwise adversely affect the rights of the other Parties in and to this Agreement or the assets covered hereby. 8.2 Assignment. Neither Party may assign its rights or obligations hereunder without the prior written consent of the other Party; provided, that either Party may collaterally assign this Agreement to any Secured Party, or such entity's agent, in connection with a financing or a refinancing that is directly or indirectly secured in whole or in part by the WindCo Project or the StorageCo Project, as applicable, and any actual assignment or transfer to another party arising from the realization upon any such collateral assignment (including, without limitation, any purchaser at a foreclosure sale) shall also be permitted without the prior written consent of the other Party, provided that any such assignee agrees, in writing and in a form reasonably satisfactory to the non-assigning Party, to be bound by the terms and conditions of this Agreement. In connection with the collateral assignment of this Agreement pursuant to the financing of the StorageCo Project, StorageCo agrees to use commercially reasonable efforts to obtain a non-disturbance agreement for the benefit of WindCo from the collateral agent in its financing and, upon the collateral assignment of this Agreement pursuant to any financing of the WindCo Project, WindCo agrees to undertake the same for the benefit of StorageCo. This Agreement shall be binding upon and inure to the benefit of successors and permitted assigns of the Parties hereto. 8.3 Interference. Subject to the terms of this Agreement, in no event shall either Party be entitled to exercise its rights to access and utilize the Shared Facilities and Shared Premises in a manner that materially interferes with or limits the reasonable and necessary access and utilization of the Shared Facilities and Shared Premises by the other Party as provided for in this Agreement. 8.4 Estoppels; Consents; Etc. In connection with the financing or sale of each Project, each Party (including the Shared Facilities Manager) will, upon the reasonable request of a Party, provide customary estoppels and consents in favor of lenders or other finance parties, including rights of step-in with respect to a Party s obligations under this Agreement and rights to concurrent notice of an Event of Default. Each Party shall also reasonably cooperate with the other Parties in the making of any filings required by such requesting Party for regulatory compliance or Laws, and in the operation and maintenance of a requesting Party s Project, all solely at the expense of the requesting Party. 8.5 Preservation of Land Rights During the Term of this Agreement, WindCo will not, without the prior written consent of StorageCo, take affirmative measures to terminate the land rights to the property upon which the Shared Facilities are located, nor take any action that could reasonably be expected to have an adverse effect on the rights or obligations of the Parties under this Agreement. WindCo agrees to provide StorageCo with written Notice of any notice of termination, or threat to terminate, the real property rights underlying the Shared Facilities within ten (10) business days of StorageCo s receipt of same. WindCo agrees that StorageCo may cure any such default alleged in such Notice relating to the termination of land rights and be reimbursed by WindCo for costs incurred in curing the default, including reasonable attorney fees, within forty-five (45) days following receipt of StorageCo s invoice and supporting documentation. ARTICLE IX DEFAULT AND REMEDIES 9.1 Events of Default; Default. The following shall each constitute a default by a Party under this Agreement (an Event of Default ): (a) failure by a Party to pay in full any amount due and payable hereunder following a 30-day grace period upon written notice, or any monetary judgment awarded by a court of competent jurisdiction which is not being appealed within sixty (60) days of such judgment, where such failure is not cured within thirty (30) days after written notice of such failure, provided, however, that such period shall be extended for so long as the defaulting Party is disputing in good faith such amount pursuant to the procedures set forth in Article 7; (b) a Bankruptcy Event occurs with respect to such Party; (c) levy, seizure, assignment or sale of a substantial part of the property of a Party for or by any creditor (other than the Secured Parties) or Governmental Authority that materially affects the rights of the other Party under this Agreement or the Shared Facilities Manager s ability to perform under this Agreement, but, for the avoidance of doubt, specifically excluding any assignment for, or foreclosures, sales, assignments or transfers in lieu of foreclosure, exercise of other remedies or any other actions undertaken by, a Party s Secured Parties; (d) a representation or warranty made by a Party under this Agreement was false or misleading in any material respect when made, where the material adverse effects of or relating to such representation or warranty are not cured within thirty (30) days after written notice thereof from the non-defaulting Party; provided, that if such Party has commenced and is diligently pursuing such cure and provides the other parties with adequate assurance of due performance, the cure period shall be extended to not more than one hundred eighty (180) days after the written notice of default, as shall be necessary for such Party to cure such material adverse effect with all due diligence and dispatch; and (e) a breach by a Party in observing or performing any of its material obligations set forth in this Agreement, other than those described in clauses (a) through (e) above; provided such breach is not cured within thirty (30) days after written notice thereof from the non-defaulting Party; and provided further that if such Party has commenced and is diligently pursuing such cure and provides the other parties with adequate assurance of due performance, the cure period shall be extended to not more than one hundred eighty (180) days after the written notice of default, as shall be necessary for such Party to cure the breach with all due diligence and dispatch. 9.2 Remedies. In addition to all other remedies permitted by Law or equity or under this Agreement (all of which will be cumulative), following an Event of Default: (a) The non-defaulting Party and such Party s Secured Parties or other interest holders will be entitled following an Event of Default to perform the obligations of the defaulting Party, and the defaulting Party will reimburse the performing Party for its expenses, which it incurred in rendering the performance, plus interest at the Default Rate. In the event the non-defaulting Party incurs expenses in rendering such performance, until the non-defaulting Party is reimbursed pursuant to the preceding sentence, the non-defaulting Party shall have a lien on the defaulting Party s ownership interests in the Shared Facilities and Shared Premises, to the extent of any such unreimbursed expenses. (b) The Parties agree that damages may be an inadequate remedy for an Event of Default under this Agreement, and that each Party will be entitled to seek injunctive and other equitable relief against the other Party to prevent or eliminate such default, or to enforce the provisions of this Agreement. ARTICLE X REPRESENTATIONS AND WARRANTIES As of the Effective Date, each Party represents and warrants for the benefit of the other Parties as follows: It is a limited liability company or corporation, duly organized and existing in good standing under the laws of the state of its formation or incorporation, qualified to do business in the Commonwealth of Pennsylvania, and has the requisite power and authority to enter into this Agreement. This Agreement has been duly authorized and constitutes the legal, valid and binding obligation of it, enforceable against it in accordance with its terms; and the execution and delivery of this Agreement and, except as otherwise set forth herein, performance of its obligations hereunder will not require the approval of any Governmental Authority and will not contravene, conflict with or result in the breach or violation of any document to which it is bound or in any law, rule or regulation. Except as otherwise set forth herein, it possesses all requisite power and authority and required permits, consents and licenses (if any) to perform this Agreement and to carry out the transactions contemplated herein. No suit, action or arbitration, or legal, administrative or other proceeding is pending or, to its knowledge, threatened against it that would affect the validity or enforceability of this Agreement or the ability of it to fulfill its obligations and commitments hereunder. ARTICLE XI GENERAL PROVISIONS 11.1 Notices. Any notices, statements, demands, correspondence or other communications required or permitted to be given hereunder will be in writing and will be given (a) personally; (b) by electronic mail delivery; or (c) by overnight or other courier or delivery service, freight prepaid, to the recipient party s address shown beneath such party s signature block to this Agreement. Notices delivered by hand or by electronic mail delivery will be deemed received when delivered, and notices sent by overnight or other courier or delivery service will be deemed received on the first to occur of: (i) two (2) business days after deposit in the United States mail or with such overnight or other courier or delivery service, addressed to such address or addresses, (ii) written acceptance of delivery by the recipient or (iii) written rejection of delivery by the recipient. 11.2 Third Party Beneficiaries. Except as otherwise provided herein, the covenants contained herein are made solely for the benefit of the Parties (including the Shared Facilities Manager) and their respective successors and permitted assigns, and will not be construed as having been intended to benefit any person or entity who is not a party to this Agreement. 11.3 Amendment. Any changes to this Agreement shall require the written agreement of all of the Parties (including the Shared Facilities Manager). 11.4 Confidentiality. For purposes of this Agreement, Confidential Information will mean (i) the contents of this Agreement, (ii) any information or documentation disclosed or provided by a Party regarding the Projects or such Party s proprietary processes, technical information and know-how, management policies, economic policies, and financial and other data, (iii) all notes, reports, documents, analyses, compilations, forecasts, studies and other materials of each Party that reflect any of the foregoing, and the substance of any discussions relating thereto, and (iv) any other confidential or proprietary information of a Party or its Affiliates or any of its or their representatives relating to this Agreement and revealed to any other Party or its Affiliates or any of its or their representatives during the Term and designated in writing as confidential at the time of such disclosure, and the content or substance of such information, including economic data, load data, market information, and other pricing information. From and after the Agreement Date, a Party receiving Confidential Information (such Party, the Recipient Party ) from any other Party (such Party, the Disclosing Party ) agrees that it will use the Confidential Information only for the following purposes, and will have no right to use and will not use at any time any part of the Confidential Information directly or indirectly for any other purpose whatsoever: (i) monitoring and assessing the Disclosing Party s creditworthiness and performance security obligations under this Agreement; (ii) assessing or enforcing the Recipient Party s rights or assessing or performing its obligations under this Agreement; (iii) any proposed financing of the development, construction and operation of the Shared Facilities or a Project, including in connection with the listing of any shares, stocks, securities, bonds or any other similar financial instrument, but in each case only to the extent reasonably required in connection with obtaining such financing; and (iv) the sale of any right, title, or interest in the Shared Facilities or a Project by a Party. The Recipient Party agrees that it will not, without the prior written consent of the Disclosing Party, disclose any Confidential Information to any Person other than to the Recipient Party s Related Parties having a need to know such information for the purpose set forth above, or in the case of a financing, to such Party s proposed lenders or investors and such parties Related Parties, or in the case of a sale, to such proposed purchasers, and then only on condition that each such Related Party or permitted recipient will be bound by the restrictions of this Section 11.4 to the same extent as the Recipient Party and that the Recipient Party will be liable to the other Parties for any breach by any such Related Party of the restrictions set forth in this Section 11.4. If the Recipient Party or any of its Related Parties is requested or required in any legal or regulatory proceeding or process (including, without limitation, pursuant to any request under any state or federal public disclosure law to which the Recipient Party or any of its Related Parties may be subject, or the requirements of any securities exchange) to disclose any Confidential Information, the Recipient Party will, except as and to the extent prohibited by applicable law or regulation, promptly notify the Disclosing Party of such request or requirement so that the Disclosing Party may take steps to resist, clarify or narrow such request or requirement and seek an appropriate protective order or other reliable assurances of nondisclosure, and the Recipient Party will cooperate reasonably with the Disclosing Party, at the Disclosing Party s cost and expense, in connection therewith. If, in the absence of a protective order or waiver from the Disclosing Party hereunder, the Recipient Party or its Related Parties are compelled to disclose any Confidential Information or else stand liable for contempt or suffer other civil or criminal liability, the Recipient Party and its Related Parties may disclose only such Confidential Information, and then only to the Person compelling disclosure, as is in the opinion of Recipient Party s counsel required by law and, in connection with such compelled disclosure, the Recipient Party and its Related Parties will use their commercially reasonable efforts, at the Disclosing Party s cost and expense, to obtain from any Person to which disclosure is made written assurance that confidential treatment will be accorded to such Confidential Information. The provisions of this Section 11.4 will not be applicable to information which (i) is or becomes generally available to the public other than as a direct or indirect result of an intentional or inadvertent disclosure by the Recipient Party or any Related Parties of the Recipient Party or anyone to whom the Recipient Party or any of its Related Parties transmits the information, (ii) was available to the Recipient Party prior to its disclosure to the Recipient Party by the Disclosing Party or any of the Disclosing Party s Related Parties, provided that such information is not known to the Recipient Party, after due inquiry, to be subject to another confidentiality agreement with, or other obligation of secrecy to, the Disclosing Party or another party, (iii) becomes available to the Recipient Party from a source other than the Disclosing Party or any of the Disclosing Party s Related Parties, provided that such source is not known to the Recipient Party, after due inquiry, to be subject to another confidentiality agreement with, or other obligation of secrecy to, the Disclosing Party or another party, or (iv) is independently developed by the Recipient Party, other than in connection with this Agreement. The Recipient Party acknowledges that a monetary remedy for a breach of this Section 11.4 will be inadequate and will be impracticable and extremely difficult to prove, and that any such breach would cause the Disclosing Party irreparable harm. In the event of such a breach, in addition to any other available rights and remedies, the Disclosing Party will be entitled to seek temporary and permanent injunctive relief, including temporary restraining orders, preliminary injunctions and permanent injunctions, without the necessity of posting a bond or making any undertaking in connection therewith and without the necessity of proving actual damages. Any such requirement of a bond or undertaking is hereby waived by the Recipient Party, and the Recipient Party acknowledges that in the absence of such a waiver, a bond or undertaking might be required by the court. Upon (i) the expiration or termination for any reason of this Agreement, (ii) the delivery at any time by the Disclosing Party to the Recipient Party of a written notice or demand requesting the return or destruction of the Confidential Information to the Disclosing Party, or (iii) the occurrence of an Event of Default with respect to the Recipient Party, the Recipient Party will immediately return to the Disclosing Party or destroy any and all Confidential Information and all other materials related thereto at its own cost and expense; and the Recipient Party will not thereafter make any use whatsoever of any Confidential Information; provided, however, that the Recipient Party will be entitled to retain a copy of any such Confidential Information as is required to satisfy the document retention requirements of any applicable law or regulation, internal policy or securities exchange. The obligations of the Parties under this Section 11.4 will continue for a period of two (2) years from and after the expiration or termination of this Agreement. 11.5 Integration.
