This Agreement contains all agreements of the Parties with respect to the subject matter hereof, and except as otherwise indicated herein, all other prior agreements, understandings, correspondence and negotiations between or among any one or more of the Parties, whether oral or written, pertaining to the subject matter of this Agreement, will be of no further force or effect, and are superseded hereby including, without limitation, the Original Agreement. 11.6 Severability. The invalidity or unenforceability of any provision hereof as determined by a court of competent jurisdiction will in no way affect the validity and enforceability of any other provision hereof; and in the event that any part or provision of this Agreement will be determined by a court of competent jurisdiction to be invalid or unenforceable, then the remaining portions of this Agreement which can be separated from the invalid, unenforceable provisions will, nevertheless, continue in full force and effect. 11.7 Further Assurances; Cooperation. Each of the Parties will, from time to time, execute, cause to be acknowledged and deliver such documents or instruments, and provide such certificates, as any other party to this Agreement may reasonably request to carry out and fulfill the transactions, and permit the exercise and performance of the rights and obligations, as are contemplated hereunder. Each of the Parties will cooperate with each other to effectuate fully the purposes and intent of this Agreement. 11.8 Successors and Assigns. The Shared Facilities will be held and used subject to the covenants, terms and provisions set forth in this Agreement, and such covenants, terms and provisions will run with the land, and will be binding upon and inure to the benefit of each of the Parties and each other person and entity having any interest therein during their ownership thereof, and their respective permitted grantees, heirs, successors and permitted assigns, and will create privity of contract and estate among the Parties and their respective grantees, heirs, successors and permitted assigns. 11.9 Nature of Relationship Between Parties. The Parties hereby declare that the Party s relationship in and to the Shared Facilities and Shared Premises is and will be that of owner in the case of WindCo and licensee in the case of StorageCo, expressly subject, however, to the terms, conditions, limitations and requirements set forth in this Agreement. Nothing contained in this Agreement will be deemed to constitute the Parties as partners or joint venturers. 11.10 Waiver of Partition. The Parties will not have and hereby waive the right to partition all or any portion of the Shared Facilities, or to make application to any court or authority or to commence or prosecute any action or proceeding for partition of the Shared Facilities. Each Party will be entitled to a decree or order restraining or enjoining such partition, application, action or proceeding upon any breach of the provisions of this Section 11.10. The Parties acknowledge and agree that they have been paid full consideration for the waiver herein provided. 11.11 Construction. This Agreement will be subject to, governed by, and construed in accordance with the Laws of the State of New York. This Agreement will be construed equally as between the parties hereto, and will not be construed against the party responsible for the drafting of this Agreement. Captions in this Agreement are inserted for convenience of reference only, and do not define, describe or limit the scope or intent of this Agreement or any of the terms hereof. No remedy or election of or by any party hereunder will be deemed exclusive, but will, wherever possible, be cumulative with all other remedies available hereunder, at law or in equity. As used herein, the neuter gender includes the masculine and the feminine, the singular number includes the plural, and vice versa and including means including, but not limited to and other forms of the verb to include are to be interpreted similarly. Time is of the essence with respect to the obligations to be performed under this Agreement. All Exhibits and Schedules attached hereto are hereby incorporated herein by this reference. 11.12 Waiver. The waiver by any party of any covenant contained herein will not be deemed a continuing waiver of such covenant or of any other covenant contained herein, or of any subsequent breach by any other party. No party s acceptance of a payment or performance by any other party will be deemed a waiver of any preceding breach by such other party of any provisions hereof. Any waiver hereunder must be in a writing signed by such waiving party. 11.13 Survival. Any obligations referred to herein to be performed at any time after the expiration or termination of this Agreement, and all indemnities and hold harmless agreements provided herein, will survive the expiration or earlier termination of this Agreement. 11.14 Counterparts. This Agreement may be executed in one or more counterparts, each of which when so executed will be deemed an original, and all of which when taken together will constitute one and the same instrument.
